subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
Montane and submontane grasslands, typically in wetlands with long rank grass and, at higher elevations, sparser and shorter grasses. Where the South East African Vlei Rat co-occurs with the Southern African Vlei Rat (
O. irroratus
), they are associated with plants on wetter soils, and the Angoni Vlei Rat (
O. angoniensis
) is associated with drier habitats further away from water.
